	<text>
		<body xml:lang="en">
			<div>

	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_002203_0001"/><!--pb/@n='43r'-->
<!--printed letterhead--><!--
<p rend="center">Newstead Abbey,</p>
<p rend="center">Mansfield, Notts.</p>
--><!--printed letterhead ends here-->
<lb/><p rend="center"><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>24 Feb<hi rend="sup">y</hi> 1865</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">My Dear <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Murray</persName></p>
<lb/><p><space extent="1" unit="chars"/>Your friend 
<lb/>makes a good 
<lb/>many corrections 
<lb/>which make the 
<lb/>matters spoken of 
<lb/>in some cases 
<lb/>much clearer<reg>.</reg>
<lb/>I had sent off the 
<lb/>proofs of the 
<lb/>parts he corrects 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_002203_0002"/><!--pb/@n='43v'-->
<lb/>corrected and now 
<lb/>send these to <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Clowes</persName>
<lb/>with a note at the 
<lb/>top requesting him 
<lb/>to incorporate the 
<lb/>new corrections 
<lb/>with those previously 
<lb/>sent. I found it 
<lb/>necessary to make 
<lb/>considerable additions 
<lb/>to the account of 
<lb/>Kebrabasa as a 
<lb/><persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Stewart</persName> in "Good 
<lb/>words" said that 
<lb/>I had not been 
<lb/>examined from 
<lb/>end to end - and 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_002203_0003"/><!--pb/@n='44r'-->
<lb/>that was done at 
<lb/>no little toil and 
<lb/>pain. When that 
<lb/>part comes back 
<lb/>I have fair sailing 
<lb/>but am a little 
<lb/>dazed<reg>.</reg></p>
<lb/><p>I enclose a 
<lb/>letter from <persName>M<hi rend="sup">rs</hi> L</persName>
<lb/>which I enclose 
<lb/>that you may see 
<lb/>exactly what she 
<lb/>says - 1<hi rend="sup">st</hi> &amp; 2<hi rend="sup">nd</hi> pages 
<lb/>are what you 
<lb/>require to look at 
<lb/>chiefly - the Yankees 
<lb/>have married 
<lb/>me in one part 

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_002203_0004"/><!--pb/@n='44v'-->
<lb/>at <placeName>Constantinople</placeName><reg>.</reg></p>
<lb/><p rend="center"><space extent="1" unit="chars"/>I am &amp;c</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>David Livingstone</p>
			
</div>
